  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the<strong> chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1628782750178-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1628782750178-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1628782750178-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1628782750178-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1628782750178-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> ground paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>dried oregano </strong>and<strong> ground allspice </strong>to a plate with 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g] </span><strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a few grinds of <strong>black pepper </strong>and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>flour & spice mix</strong></p><p>Crack the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a separate bowl and beat with a fork</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628782837701-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628782837701-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628782837701-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628782837701-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628782837701-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop each <strong>chicken breast</strong> into 4 strips</p><p>Coat the <strong>chicken strips</strong> in the <strong>flour & spice mix</strong>, tap off the excess, then add them into the beaten egg</p><p>Once all the chicken pieces are coated in the egg, return them to the remaining <strong>flour & spice</strong> <strong>mix</strong> to coat in a second layer – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
